Britain and Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) countries are negotiating a free-trade agreement, Britain's investment minister Gerry Grimstone said on Monday, according to Reuters. A deal will be concluded within 12 months, Grimstone said at a conference in Dubai. The GCC is already an important trading partner for Britain, with almost £22 billion ($29.57 billion) of British exports and bilateral trade worth over £30 billion in 2020, showed a British government website.